## **International Title Shot 4-Way: Ricochet & Speedball Bailey def. Mark Davis & Orange Cassidy**

![](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5d56e145f80b7500016ba502/7233c6d5-9e54-46c5-8c50-4b7a2c23506f/GmcZgehWUAAJpJc.png?format=original)

Controversial finish in the 4-way match for the International Title shot against Kenny Omega. Speedball Bailey had Mark Davis rolled up and Ricochet jumped in on the pin attempt. Due to a double pinfall... BOTH RICOCHET AND MIKE BAILEY GET THE TITLE SHOT!!!!

Kenny Omega vs Ricochet vs Speedball Bailey in a 3-way match at AEW Dynasty for the International Title!

#  **TBS Championship: (C)Mercedes Mone def. Billie Starkz**

![](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5d56e145f80b7500016ba502/9578c726-f400-4fee-a429-6345d02398e9/GmcbXHFa8AEwcKo.jpg?format=original)

Billie had an exceptional showing and she was VERY CLOSE to taking the title! The experience of Mercedes was too much for Billie, though. Mone catches Starkz in the Statement Maker for the win. Billie doesn't lose the match looking bad by any means, though!

##  **AEW Championship: (C)Jon Moxley def. COPE**

![](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5d56e145f80b7500016ba502/20e3e9a0-4e01-4a0c-bdfa-0a3039181a76/GmckYKhaYAAt1Br.jpg?format=original)

Match starts backstage where Cope fights Moxley through a supply truck and the backstage area. They come out to the ringside area where we get tables, chairs, Mox getting thrown onto Tony Schiavone… and then SPIKE! Cope slams Moxley down onto spike… WHICH STAYS EMBEDDED IN MOXLEY’S BACK! Death Riders try to attack and help Moxley, but FTR save the day. Cope spears Mox through a table! Shafir stops the pin, but Willow then takes Marina out of the equation.

Nick Wayne & Kip Sabian take down Cope on behalf of Christian Cage. Moxley secures the win. Prince Nana is watching backstage and makes a call to someone… Swerve vs Moxley for the World Championship is now confirmed for Dynasty! As Cope gets back up, Dax Harwood walks out on his partner, Cope, and Willow.

## Will Ospreay def. AR Fox

![](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5d56e145f80b7500016ba502/a2833f66-5d86-4957-a9e7-4c49bce05872/GmcomGDaAAAWFc7.jpg?format=original)

With the storms shifting matches around, we manage to get AR Fox and Will Ospreay in an epic battle where they ABSOLUTELY COOK!!! Fox misses a 450 splash, but Ospreay moves out of the way to secure the Hidden Blade for the victory!

## Megan Bayne def. Kris Statlander

![](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5d56e145f80b7500016ba502/cc26dba0-c4bf-4ec1-9408-6e1988ca917d/GmcwkkebAAAZn45.jpg?format=original)

Timeless Toni Storm is out on commentary. This is a VERY physical match between two of the strongest women in AEW! Megan Bayne rolls up Stat for the victory. After the match, Toni Storm tapes up her fists and gets in the ring where Storm & Bayne fight! Security runs in to try and break it up. Toni Storm says that her and Megan "Shall have a date at Dynasty!"